cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CY. 

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques applied to community question answering data for product-related questions. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also involves information retrieval techniques, which makes cs.IR (Information Retrieval) a likely category as well. The use of machine learning models for transfer learning and classification makes cs.LG (Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely categories. Finally, the paper also involves the use of mobile-based shopping assistants, which could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society).
